
Not completely startled, I didn't let my gaze drop. I had another question on my mind, heaving over my.
"Did you, or did you not kill Vince Mascars' mother?"
Zach's eyes shot back up, wide and anxious at my face. "Zoe-"
"Did you?"
He paused, his eyes filled with regret and terror. "...I did."
A tear finally slipped out. I didn't know what to think.
"I-" I started. "I..."
There wasn't anything left to say. Nothing came to my mind.
Unable to take it anymore, I quietly grabbed the two crumpled pieces of paper and walked out the front door.